USAGE

	qrins -i <reads_fastq_directory_path> 
	      -t <read1_tag, default '_R1_'>
          -p <read2_tag, default '_R2_'>
	      -n <project_name>
	      -a <actions_file>
	      -w <bowtie_indexed_human_reference, default /ax3-cgi/resources/reference/eukaryote/human/hs37d5/bowtie_indexed/hs37d5>
	      -o <blat_indexed_human_reference, default /ax3-cgi/resources/reference/eukaryote/human/hs37d5/hs37d5.2bit>
	      -O <ooc_file_for_human_reference, default /ax3-cgi/resources/reference/eukaryote/human/hs37d5/blat_indexed/hs37d5.11.ooc>
	      -d <blast_indexed_human_reference, default /ax3-cgi/resources/reference/eukaryote/human/hs37d5/blast_indexed/hs37d5>
	      -D <blast_indexed_nt_database, default /ax3-cgi/resources/reference/nt/nt.fa>
	      -x <taxonomy_dmp_file, default /ax3-cgi/resources/taxonomy/gi_taxid_nucl.dmp>


DESCRIPTION

	-i	Absolute path to a a directory containing 
                a set of fastq files or a CGI project directory
                containing fastq files organised into sample 
                sub-folders. The fastq files need to have the .fq.gz
                or .fastq.gz extension.

	-t	The tag of the fastq file containing read1
		sequences, default is  _R1_.

	-p	The tag of the fastq file containing read2
		sequences, default is _R2_.

	-n	Project name.

	-a 	Absolute path to the actions file
		default /groupvol/cgi/src/pathogen/trunk/imsa/actions.txt

	-w 	Absolute path to the bowtie-indexed human reference
		default /ax3-cgi/resources/reference/eukaryote/human/hs37d5/bowtie_indexed/hs37d5

	-o 	Absolute path to the blat-indexed human reference
		default /ax3-cgi/resources/reference/eukaryote/human/hs37d5/hs37d5.2bit

	-O 	Absolute path to the ooc file for human_reference
		default /ax3-cgi/resources/reference/eukaryote/human/hs37d5/blat_indexed/hs37d5.11.ooc

	-d 	Absolute path to the blast-indexed human reference
		default /ax3-cgi/resources/reference/eukaryote/human/hs37d5/blast_indexed/hs37d5

	-D 	Absolute path to the blast-indexed nt database
		default /ax3-cgi/resources/reference/nt/nt.fa

	-x 	Absolute path to the taxonomy dmp file
		default /ax3-cgi/resources/taxonomy/gi_taxid_nucl.dmp

	-h	Display help and exit.
